Text Editor Web Application
Welcome to the Text Editor Web Application! This application allows you to create and store notes or code snippets, with or without an internet connection. Whether you're online or offline, you can reliably access and retrieve your content for later use.

Features
PWA (Progressive Web Application)
IndexedDB Integration
Deployment to Render

To get started with the Text Editor Web Application, follow these steps:

Clone this repository to your local machine.
Install dependencies by running npm install.
Start the development server by running npm run start.
Open your browser and navigate to the specified URL to access the application.

Usage
Once the application is running, you can:

Create new notes or code snippets.
Edit and update your content.
Save your content locally using IndexedDB.
Access your saved content offline.
Install the application as a PWA for easy access.
Deployment
To deploy the Text Editor Web Application to Render:

Ensure that your .npmrc file is included in the project.
Follow the Render Deployment Guide provided on The Full-Stack Blog.
Configure your Render environment and deploy your application.

Contributing
Contributions are welcome! If you'd like to contribute to this project, feel free to submit a pull request or open an issue on GitHub.

